{
  "analysis": "`BH` is installed and visible to Rscript, but `stan_model` still reports “Boost not found”. This suggests RStan's compilation configuration is not detecting the `BH` include path, possibly because `BH` is installed in `/usr/lib/R/site-library` while RStan is in `/usr/local/lib/R/site-library`, or because a stale cached compiled model directory exists. I need inspect `.libPaths()`, `BH` package path, and RStan system files for the Boost detection logic.",
  "plan": "I will run a diagnostic R script to print `.libPaths()`, `BH` and `StanHeaders` locations/versions, and the RStan include/detection configuration. I will also check for any cached Stan model files in `/tmp` or `/app`. This will identify why Boost is not found despite `BH` being installed.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "Rscript -e 'library(rstan); print(.libPaths()); cat(\"BH:\\n\"); print(packageDescription(\"BH\", fields=c(\"Package\",\"Version\",\"Location\"))); cat(\"StanHeaders:\\n\"); print(packageDescription(\"StanHeaders\", fields=c(\"Package\",\"Version\",\"Location\"))); cat(\"rstan:\\n\"); print(packageDescription(\"rstan\", fields=c(\"Package\",\"Version\",\"Location\"))); cat(\"rstan:::BoostDir?\\n\"); tryCatch(print(body(rstan:::BoostDir)), error=function(e) print(e)); cat(\"system file includes:\\n\"); print(list.files(system.file(\"include\", package=\"rstan\"), recursive=FALSE))'\n",
      "duration": 1.0
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "find /app /tmp -name '*hierarchical_model*' -o -name '*.stan' -o -name '*stan*cache*' 2>/dev/null | head -50\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "grep -R \"Boost not found\" /usr/local/lib/R/site-library/rstan /usr/lib/R/site-library/rstan 2>/dev/null | head -20\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    }
  ]
}
